wikipedia_page.main: Juliet Camilla Frankland  (née Brown, 30 January 1929 – 9 June 2013), was a British botanist and mycologist, and "a world expert on fungi".

response: She was the elder daughter of Walter Henry Brown (1893/4–1956), a Ministry of Works civil servant, and his wife, Gerda Lois Brown, née Grenside (1885–1961), an artist. Her sister was the mycologist, Juliet Frankland.
